That can be a very powerful cycle that will definitely change how you interact with all around you.

Tell us about the charity and project you manage called ‘La Primavera’.

There is a beautiful sculpture in my small paraguayan town called “La Primavera”, so nice that it looks like it took someone’s life to sculpt it. It also always has a story for every season. I decided to write about these stories to promote “La Primavera.” The blog I run exists to provide a community for Paraguayans to unite through art in all of its variations. The first post tells truly the story of the site, about my ambition behind it all. While the site might not seem like much to the general viewer, to me it represents the effort I’ve put in it, the people that I’ve gotten to know writing for me, how the project has united my community, and has allowed me to organise art I never knew I had in me.

What motivates you on a daily basis / what drives you to do the work that you do?
